<br>
If you are a HardCore Everquest player, please read on.<br>
<br>
Do you think you know every zone in Norrath like the<br>
back of your hand? Do you know every tree to hide behind,<br>
every NPC, every quest that is useful, every uber item?<br>
Do you think you can level up faster than the rest of them?<br>
Do you think you can make the trades to get the items to<br>
outfit yourself with gear that will make you near invincible<br>
to the next guy? <br>
<br>
Why don't you try to test your mettle in the toughest yet<br>
most rewarding environment in all of EverQuest.<br>
<br>
Sullon Zek.<br>
<br>
This server is the only server in all of EverQuest with<br>
a 20% experience bonus for all creatures. It has the fastest<br>
leveling out of all 40+ other servers except for one small<br>
factor.  100s of people will be gunning for you once you<br>
pass level 6.  If you think you can tough it out and want<br>
to play on a server that was so tough Verant had to halve<br>
the death penalty and increase the xp why not give it a <br>
try.  This is HardCore EverQuest.  This is real RolePlaying<br>
where the deities you chose are a matter of life and death.<br>
<br>
This is the only server in Everquest that has real zone<br>
control.  It is the only server in all of EverQuest that<br>
has a point system where your name can be in lights at<br>
the end of the day on Sony's web site.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/stats/sz_summary.jsp">everquest.station.sony.co...ummary.jsp</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
It is one of the only servers that every night has player<br>
created dynamic events like no other. Guildwars that<br>
cross many zones. Evils trying to stop goods from getting<br>
their cleric Epics. No cross teaming. Very little twinking.<br>
And a place where reputation matters because you only have<br>
one character per account. <br>
<br>
This server is the place where real role-playing occurs,<br>
there is no grouping or guilding between teams, only war,<br>
competition and fun. Every night is a GM event night<br>
because the players create it. Just running through a zone<br>
can be an adventure when in enemy territory.  Going AFK is<br>
a dangerous thing, the unexpected can happen, unlike regular<br>
EQ.<br>
<br>
Are you bored of 6 hour dragon raids where one person<br>
gets something which only increases their STR by 4 points?<br>
Why not go on a server where you can make your own fun<br>
by raiding into enemy lands and killing for passion or<br>
for platinum?  On Sullon Zek, you will have to create<br>
a completely different set of gear for resists against players,<br>
it adds a completely different dimension to game play beyond<br>
what typical EverQuest can offer.  You can make your own<br>
Legends there and you don't need a special 40 dollar server.<br>
<br>
Every zone has the possibility of an Uber encounter when<br>
enemies raid the lands. And the mobs that attack are real<br>
people with smarts and strategy that no AI could ever compete<br>
with.   Camps are rarely boring when at any moment enemy's<br>
could come out of the woodwork and challenge your group<br>
to battle.   You will not be able to level up in the<br>
same 3 or 4 zones you are used to, you will have to move<br>
and learn new places, new things, new techniques to get<br>
around the team zone control.<br>
<br>
<br>
If you want it easy go on the evil team, they own most of Kunark and<br>
level easily without disturbances usually, they are also the largest<br>
team. If you want it hard but not impossible go on the neutral team.  <br>
If you want the highest challenge of all, go on the good team<br>
they are the smallest team but hardy players, every one. Read up<br>
on the rules carefully and choose a class carefully.<br>
<br>
Try it, you'll like it, it is like a whole new Everquest.<br>
<br>
All for the regular EQ price, you can make your own Legend there.<br>
<br>
Sullon Zek Deity Teams EverQuest Server.<br>
